*Assign a role to multiple users.
*Modify access for an existing user account
*Review user&rsquo;s access to system objects.

==Applicable Scenarios==
You manage user access in the following cases:[anchor|#_7165d0ed-fbf9-4bca-b563-a0155c7a9310]
*When you, as an implementation consultant, initially implement Acumatica ERP for your client and is ready to give access to company employees.
*When you, as a system administrator, was notified about a new hire and need to give appropriate access to the system for the new employee.
*When you, as a system administrator, was notified about change of a position for an employee and need to change access for this employee according to the new responsibilities.

==User Authentication and Authorization==
 Acumatica ERP requires users to authenticate by using the appropriate username and password. After successful authentication, user membership in roles is checked. Then users may access only the resources and perform only the actions they are authorized to by their roles. {br}

A user with no role assigned has no access to the system. If the user has multiple roles that have different levels of access rights to an entity, the highest level applies. {br}

Method of authentication in Acumatica ERP can be one of the following: [anchor|#_0bf517b1-a901-4736-bcd4-8609358a7c10]
*Local: User accounts are created and managed directly in Acumatica ERP. 
*External: If Acumatica ERP is integrated with an external identity management system, then user accounts and roles are created and managed in the integrated system. For details on supported integrations see, [HelpRoot_Integration\US__con_Integration_with_Active_Directory|Integration with Active Directory], [HelpRoot_Integration\US__con_ADFS_Integration|Integration with AD FS], and [HelpRoot_Integration\US__con_AzureAD_Integration|Integration with Azure Active Directory].

To make the authentication process easier for your users, you can configure single sign-on with external identity providers, such as Google and Microsoft Account. For details, see [HelpRoot_Integration\US__con_SSO_with_Google|Single Sign-On with Google] and [HelpRoot_Integration\US__con_SSO_with_Microsoft_Account|Single Sign-On with Microsoft Account].{br}

Also, Acumatica ERP provides two-factor authentication, so that access to the system is granted only after the user successfully presents to the system additional evidence of authentication in addition to the user credentials (that is, the username and password). For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\DM__mng_Two_Factor_Auth|Managing Two-Factor Authentication].
==User Account Creation==
When you configure access for users to Acumatica ERP, you perform the following steps on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form:[anchor|#_c56d62c5-d31c-4844-ab83-504e31428b0d]
#You create a user account and specify the username, password, user&rsquo;s first and last name, and email address. 
#If your organization uses specific security policies, you apply them to the user account. For more detailed information on security policies for user accounts, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SA_Managing_User_Access_User_Access_Security_Concept|User Access: User Access Security].
#You define access to the system objects by assigning set of roles that corresponds to the user&rsquo;s job responsibilities.

==Ways to Generate and Share User Credentials==
When you create a new user, the system automatically generates password for the user. That is, fills in the '''Password''' box with the masked password. You can clear the '''Generate Password''' checkbox for the new user and type a password (that can be generated by any third-party tool) to the '''Password''' box. For an existing user you can click '''Reset Password''' on the form toolbar and enter a new password for this user.{br}

If a default system email account is configured and corresponding notification templates are specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_01|Email Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM204001|SM204001]) form, the system sends an email with user credentials to the address you have specified in the '''Email''' box for the user, when you save user settings for the first time.{br}

If a system email account is not configured or you do not want to share credentials using email services, you can share credentials using third-party services you trust to. In this case, you set passwords manually for the users in Acumatica ERP and share user credentials using a third-party tool.
==Roles Assignment==
To give a user access to the system objects, you need to assign this user with a role or combination of roles which provide access necessary to perform job responsibilities. For details on user role configuration, see [HelpRoot_Administration\User_Roles_GeneralInfo|User Roles: General Information].{br}

To assign multiple roles to a selected user, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form. For example, you use this way when you have created a new user account and want to assign it existing roles.{br}

To assign multiple users a selected role, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_05|User Roles] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201005|SM201005]) form. For example, you use this way when you have created a new role and want to assign it to existing users. ((({S:Hint}You can use user types to simplify the assignment of user roles to users. For details, see[HelpRoot_Administration\SA_Managing_User_Access_User_Types_Usage_Concept|User Access: Linked Entity and User Type].
)))
==Roles Application==
To access Acumatica ERP, users must pass authentication to confirm their identity (that is, sign in the system). Then users pass authorization to determine their access rights to the system objects. Users can access only the objects they are allowed to use and perform only the actions they are authorized to based on their access rights. A user with no role assigned has no access to system. {br}

You may take different approaches in configuring user access: assigning a user with a single role or with a combination of roles. This may affect how the system calculates an individual user access. A role defines access rights to system objects with a restriction level set for these objects.[anchor|#_4f382cdf-5355-46fe-b954-d3ee691acc45]{br}

The set of restriction levels available for the system objects depends on the object type. For some objects, you can specify more granular level, for others either allow or deny the access. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\User_Roles_Access_Levels|User Roles: Restriction Level Options].{br}

If a user is assigned with a combination of roles, some of these roles may have different restriction levels set to the same system object. How the system calculates the final restriction level depends on a system object for which levels are different among roles assigned to a user. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\User_Roles_User_Access_Level_Calculation|User Roles: Calculation of Restriction Level for a User].{br}

You can view the user access rights to a particular form, containers or form element by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_55|Access Rights by User] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201055|SM201055]) form. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SA_Managing_User_Access_Reports_Inquiries|User Access: Related Report and Inquiry Forms].
==Monitoring Access Configuration==
Access configuration, once established, should be a subject or regular review and modification. People in an organization move across roles and projects or leave the company and new people hired instead. Job responsibilities for a particular employee or the whole department can be changed. You should keep the user access configuration in compliance with the company changed business processes and make sure that its sensitive data is protected from unwanted access.{br}

We recommend establishing a process of requesting an access to a particular system objects. Such requests should be justified by changes in the job responsibilities and approved by superiors.{br}

You should be notified each time when an employee is leaving the company or a contractor with a an access to the system completed their project. You can either deactivate user accounts for these people or you can clear the list of assigned roles if you need to keep a user account for some reason.{br}

Regular review of the list of user roles configured is also recommended. You can either delete unused roles that have zero people assigned or add some prefix to role description if you want to keep them for some reason. Decide for yourself what is the number of roles you can maintain to effectively secure access to the system and try keep the list within this number.{br}

Also, we recommend, regularly review history of users&rsquo; access to Acumatica ERP forms that allows viewing companies sensitive data to identify unexpected or unwanted access behavior. {br}

You can use reports and inquires provide by Acumatica ERP for monitoring access configuration. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SA_Managing_User_Access_Reports_Inquiries|User Access: Related Report and Inquiry Forms].

Users of the system may use the Acumatica mobile app to perform their job responsibilities. They just need to download the application to a mobile device and enter connection parameters: Acumatica ERP website address and user credentials. The system keeps track of only those devices for which a user allowed push notifications from the app. ==Registering Mobile Devices== If a user of the system is using the Acumatica mobile app and allowed push notifications from the app for a device, the information about such device is stored in their Acumatica ERP user profile (the '''Devices''' tab of the [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\SM_20_30_10|User Profile] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203010|SM203010]) form). {br}
When a user signs in to the mobile app for the first time, the application sends details about the device to Acumatica ERP, and then the information is updated with each subsequent sign-in. {br}
The system administrator can manage registered devices of a user on the '''Devices''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form. ==Deleting Mobile Devices== You can delete any registered device listed on the '''Devices''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] form by clicking it and using the standard button on the table toolbar, or you can delete all devices for a user by clicking the '''Delete All''' button on this toolbar. ==Enabling Push Notifications== Also, you can control to which devices the system can send push notifications on the '''Devices''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] form. You can use the '''Turn On Notifications''' check box to selectively allow or disallow these notifications for devices. You can also enable or disable sending push notifications for all user&rsquo;s devices by clicking the '''Enable All''' and '''Disable All''' buttons, respectively, on the table toolbar. {br}
If push notifications are disabled for a device, the owner of this device will not be able to use the following functionality that uses push notifications:[anchor|#_48286e4c-14ad-4f18-986c-dbb426889d8e] *Receiving a push notification if a business event occurred. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SA_Using_Business_Events_Mapref|Using Business Events]. *Uploading images to Acumatica ERP using a mobile device. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\DM__mng_File_Attachements|Managing Attached Files]. *Using two-factor authentication. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\DM__mng_Two_Factor_Auth|Managing Two-Factor Authentication].
==Tracking User Location== In Acumatica ERP, you can view the GPS location coordinates of users that are tracked through their mobile devices. To be able to view a user&rsquo;s coordinates in the system, you have to configure location tracking for each necessary user on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form. You use the '''Location Tracking''' tab to turn on the tracking functionality for the selected user, specify the time and distance intervals at which the coordinates will be tracked in the system, and specify on which days and during which time periods the system registers the user location. For detailed instructions on how to turn on and configure the location tracking, see [HelpRoot_Administration\SM__HOW_To_Turn_on_Location_Tracking|To Turn On Location Tracking of a User].((({S:Warn}For GPS location coordinates to be tracked, on the user&rsquo;s device, GPS location recording has to be switched on. ))) You can view the history of the location coordinates of all users that have been tracked in the system on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_20_00|Location Tracking History] ([~/?ScreenId=SM202000|SM202000]) form.

In Acumatica ERP, a ''linked entity'' is an employee or contact account that is associated with the user. If the user you are creating is already defined in the system as an employee or contact account, you can select the appropriate employee or contact name in this box. This will cause relevant elements to be filled in. {br}
User types are used to provide default settings for new users that you create. You can define the set of roles that are available for a user of the type and the default roles to be assigned when a user of this type is created. {br}
Also, your company may need to give your partners limited access to Acumatica ERP—for instance, to facilitate the process of entering contacts or customer orders. In such a scenario, you may need some way to segregate users that are internal to your company from external users, or even to give your partners the means to create and manage their own users in Acumatica ERP, thus freeing your administrators of the responsibility to manage these users. You can address these requirements through the use of user types in Acumatica ERP.{br}
In Acumatica ERP, creating a user account and an employee or contact is not the same. Contacts, employees, and users are created independently and can be associated with each other later. You can also create a user that is not associated with any user type or linked entity. ==Linked Entity for User Account== Depending on your purpose, you can select the following system entities as linked entity of the user: [anchor|#_e836f277-e429-4518-bfd4-ec6592ff6205] *''Contact'': You can assign this entity to external users, such as partners or contacts of customer or vendor organizations. *''Employee'': You can assign this entity to employees of your company and possibly to consultants that you consider part of your company.
==Default Settings Provided by User Type== If you use the user types functionality you can specify the following security settings on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_25_00|User Types] ([~/?ScreenId=EP202500|EP202500]) form that will be applied to all users of this type:[anchor|#_9fc1df49-697e-41fd-8806-da0d40d7fcbc] *Allow users with linked contacts to use their emails as their login to the system. *Force new users to change their password at the first login. *Force new users to activate their account.
For each user type, you can specify the set of roles that can be assigned to users of this type. For the procedure of adding a user type, see [HelpRoot_Administration\US__how_Add_Contact_User_Type|To Add a User Type].((({S:Warn}If you assign a user type to an existing user, the collection of roles from the user type overrides any roles that have been explicitly assigned to the user. )))[anchor|#_775858a7-972a-4226-ac5d-7e74ae894419] ==Internal User Types== An employee-related user type is associated with employees in your system. These user types are intended for users who are internal to your company (generally employees of your company and possibly consultants that you consider part of your company). ==External User Types== A contact-related user type is associated with a contact in your system. These user types are intended for users who are external to the company—for example, partners or contacts. As opposed to employee-related user types, you can use contact-related user types to delegate the right to create users, as described in [HelpRoot_Administration\US__how_Delegation_User_Creation_Rights|To Delegate the Right to Create Users].

In the following sections, you can find details about the reports, and inquiry forms, you may want to review to gather information user access configuration [anchor|#_42b0dead-9dc6-43ac-a003-b79c8c5a84dc]((({S:Warn}If you do not see a particular report or form that is described, you may have signed in to the system with a user account that does not have access rights to the report or form. Contact your system administrator to obtain access to any needed reports or forms. ))){br}{TOC} ==Reviewing Restriction Level to a System Object for a User== You can view the user access rights for a particular form, containers or form element by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_55|Access Rights by User] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201055|SM201055]) form. On the form, you select the user account for which you want to view the access level. In the left pane, you select a node that contains the nested objects (forms or form elements) you are interested in. Then in the right pane, you select the form or container and click the '''View Roles''' button on the pane toolbar. The system opens the '''View Roles''' dialog box, where you can view the access rights of the user to the selected object in the '''Computed Access Rights''' column. ==Reviewing Role Configuration== If you need to modify access to several forms for a single role, we recommend reviewing the role&rsquo;s configuration by using the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\SM_65_15_00|Access Rights by Role] ([~/?ScreenId=SM651500|SM651500]) report. The report lists access rights configured for every form in the system by a role. You can export it to Excel and prepare the list of needed modifications there. ==Reviewing Access Rights to a Form== If you need to modify access to a single form for several roles, we recommend reviewing access rights to the form by using the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\SM_65_17_00|Access Rights by Screen] ([~/?ScreenId=SM651700|SM651700]) report. The report lists access rights configured for every role in the system by a form. You can export it to Excel and prepare the list of needed modifications there. ==Reviewing Available Roles== For monitoring access configuration actuality, you can review the list of roles available in the system and user accounts assigned to each role by using the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\SM_65_10_00|Role List] ([~/?ScreenId=SM651000|SM651000]) report. ==Reviewing Roles Assigned to Users== For monitoring that users are assigned only roles that support their current job responsibilities, you can review the list of user accounts available in the system and roles assigned to each user account by using the [HelpRoot_ReportReference\SM_65_05_00|User List] ([~/?ScreenId=SM650500|SM650500]) report. ==Auditing User Activity== If you need to audit activity of a particular user, you can track the following information on the '''Statistics''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form:[anchor|#_8cdf6c92-e809-408c-ab73-c308304cc83f] *The date and time of the last login. *The most recent date when the account was temporarily locked out. *The date and time of the most recent password change. *The number of unsuccessful attempts the user made to sign into the account.
==Reviewing Access History of Users== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201060|SM201060]) form, you can select the types of events the system will monitor and set up the time period for which the audit trail must be kept.[anchor|#_5b05b43f-3496-49b3-83dd-fb4ebe20b055]{br}
You use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_45|Access History] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201045|SM201045]) form to view the audit trails. The audit trail for the event type shows the time when the event took place, the user who performed the operation, the IP address from which the user signed in to the system, and other parameters, depending on the event type. You can filter the events by user, date range, and operation type.

You use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_25_00|User Types] ([~/?ScreenId=EP202500|EP202500]) form to delegate to an external user the right to create users. This may be required if you need to give your partners the right to manage their organizations' users or customers on the Self-Service Portal of your Acumatica ERP instance.{br}
