Because Acumatica ERP holds the personal data of individuals, it should be able to comply with the requirements of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). Acumatica ERP provides GDPR compliance tools that simplify the handling of personal data and give you the ability to protect personal data and restrict its processing, if needed. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_f7262943-f984-41ee-9a71-cfed8384b044] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#_ae2a72ed-6766-437d-a068-6a1d685abb1a] *[HelpRoot_Administration\GD__CON_GDPR_Tools|Compliance Tools for General Data Protection Regulation]
| [anchor|#_d8fb392f-6746-4d7e-94c9-d2dab5fa87b7] *
|}

row.column:
Acumatica ERP provides GDPR compliance tools that enable you to do the following:[anchor|#_1d7e7b44-0994-42f3-84a6-2ee0655d729c] *Track in the system whether the consent of individuals for the processing of personal data has been obtained or recalled *Restrict the processing of personal data for particular individuals *Erase and restore personal data *Audit who restricted the processing of personal data or erased personal data in the system, when the event occurred, and what data was restricted
==Availability of GDPR Compliance Tools== GDPR compliance tools become available in the system if the ''GDPR Compliance Tools'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}
To be able to access GDPR compliance tools, you need to have the ''Data Privacy Controller'' role. This predefined role has ''View Only'' access to all forms that contain personal data. Also, it is the only role that has access (of the ''Delete'' type, which means that the role has complete access) to the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_20_10|Restrict Personal Data] ([~/?ScreenId=GD102010|GD102010]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_20_20|Erase Personal Data] ([~/?ScreenId=GD102020|GD102020]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_20_30|Restricted Personal Data] ([~/?ScreenId=GD102030|GD102030]), and [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_10_10|Privacy Tools Audit] ([~/?ScreenId=GD101010|GD101010]) forms. ==Affected Entities== In the out-of-the-box Acumatica ERP instance, GDPR compliance tools affect the following entities:[anchor|#_d4d6e792-440c-4b43-9ae6-dad8df058aae] *Business accounts, including customers, vendors, and prospects *Documents associated with business accounts, such as sales orders, invoices, and purchase orders *Contacts *Leads *Employees *Opportunities
Also, you can mark a user-defined attribute as containing personal data by selecting the '''Contains Personal Data''' check box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_20_50_00|Attributes] ([~/?ScreenId=CS205000|CS205000]) form; the values of this attribute will then be treated by the system as personal data. ==Consent Settings== To record that an individual has given his or her consent for the processing of the person&rsquo;s personal data and to specify the time interval during which the system should consider the individual&rsquo;s consent to be effective, you can use the settings in the '''Personal Data Privacy''' section, which is available on the following forms: [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\AP_30_30_00|Vendors] ([~/?ScreenId=AP303000|AP303000]), and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]).{br}
These settings can be mass-updated for leads, contacts, and business accounts through the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_30_20|Update Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503020|CR503020]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_30_21|Update Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503021|CR503021]), and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_33_20|Update Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503320|CR503320]) forms. ==Obfuscation of Personal Data== To restrict the processing of personal data for individuals whose consent has expired or has been revoked, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_20_10|Restrict Personal Data] ([~/?ScreenId=GD102010|GD102010]) form. On the form toolbar of this form, the '''Pseudonymize''' and '''Pseudonymize All''' actions are available. These actions obfuscate the personal data contained in the selected records or in all listed records, respectively, and make this data unavailable for further processing; however, this data remains stored in the database and can be restored at any time on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_20_30|Restricted Personal Data] ([~/?ScreenId=GD102030|GD102030]) form.{br}
Records with pseudonymized personal data are not shown on generic inquiry forms, and the system does not include these records in mass processes, such as the validation of records for duplicates.{br}
By using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_20_20|Erase Personal Data] ([~/?ScreenId=GD102020|GD102020]) form, you can permanently obfuscate personal data. Permanently obfuscated data cannot be restored.{br}
If the ''Scheduled Processing'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, automation schedules can be set up for the restriction or deletion of personal data. ==Restoration of Personal Data== Sometimes you may need to restore an individual&rsquo;s personal data (for instance, if the previously expired consent has been given again). You can restore obfuscated personal data by using the '''Restore''' action on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_20_30|Restricted Personal Data] ([~/?ScreenId=GD102030|GD102030]) form. The system marks an entity with restored personal data as inactive, so you may need to manually mark the needed entity as active by using the respective entry form. ==Privacy Tools Audit== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GD_10_10_10|Privacy Tools Audit] ([~/?ScreenId=GD101010|GD101010]) form, you can monitor the history of record changes, track who restricted the processing of personal data or erased personal data in the system, when this user restricted processing or erased personal data, and what data was restricted. ==Custom Fields with Personal Data== Any custom fields will be treated by the system as fields that contain personal data if all of the following conditions are met:[anchor|#_3d29f808-ce15-41de-9ceb-18a2988554d1] *<tt>PXPersonalDataTable</tt> is specified for the customized DAC or cache extension. *The <tt>PXPersonalDataField</tt> attribute is appended to the corresponding fields. *The <tt>pseudonymizationStatus</tt> class is declared, with <tt>PXPseudonymizationStatusField</tt> specified in it.

Acumatica ERP uses digital certificates to store sensitive information in the database encrypted and to authenticate documents (PDF files) that are shared or sent electronically. These certificates can be purchased from a recognized certification authority. Each certificate has a password that is used to validate the owner of the certificate if you need to reinstall the system or move the database.{br}
This topic describes the ways of using digital certificates in Acumatica ERP in more detail.{br}{TOC} ==Configuration Steps== When you want to use a digital certificate in Acumatica ERP, you do the following:[anchor|#_8c2ce3e6-0296-439d-b23b-880159caf5ec] #You import your certificate on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_30|Encryption Certificates] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200530|SM200530]) form. For a detailed procedure that describes how to import certificates, see [HelpRoot_Administration\US__How_to_Import_Digital_Certificate|To Import Certificates]. #:((({S:Hint}Digital certificates used by Acumatica ERP have the {{.pfx}} extension. Before you can import digital certificates into the system, make sure {{.pfx}} is on the list of allowed extensions on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_25_50|File Upload Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM202550|SM202550]) form. ))) #You apply the uploaded certificate to one of the following processes: #*Encrypting the database: You can replace the encryption algorithm used in Acumatica ERP to encrypt sensitive data by using your encryption certificate on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_35|Certificate Replacement] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200535|SM200535]) form. For more information, see [[#_ad9bf929-99d9-40f4-becb-c813a9e40bc2|Database Encryption]. #*Signing PDF documents: You can use the imported encryption certificate for signing PDF files generated in Acumatica ERP. You can specify a default certificate (which will be used for all PDF documents generated in Acumatica ERP) in the '''PDF Signing Certificate''' box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201060|SM201060]) form. Individual users can also select an imported certificate as a personal certificate (which overrides the default one) in the '''PDF Signing Certificate''' box on the [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\SM_20_30_10|User Profile] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203010|SM203010]) form. For details, see [[#_c05808be-e98b-42ab-a1ea-f38fefab0386|PDF Signature]. [anchor|#_ad9bf929-99d9-40f4-becb-c813a9e40bc2] ==Database Encryption== Acumatica ERP database stores sensitive data, such as credit card numbers and passwords, encrypted. If no encryption certificate is loaded, the base64-encryption is used. You can find the list of encrypted data on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_35|Certificate Replacement] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200535|SM200535]) form. You can replace the encryption algorithm used in Acumatica ERP with your encryption certificate. If the database of your Acumatica ERP instance is large, encryption may take a lot of time and may cause slowdowns in responses from the database. For large databases, we recommend that you postpone the start of encryption by scheduling it at a time when nobody uses the system (for example, at night). For a procedure that describes how to encrypt the database, see [HelpRoot_Administration\US__How_to_Encrypt_Database|To Encrypt the Database].[anchor|#_c05808be-e98b-42ab-a1ea-f38fefab0386] ==PDF Signature== You can use encryption certificates to sign PDF files generated in the system. A PDF certificate protects the authenticity of a document throughout its life cycle. For example, when a company employee emails the company&rsquo;s digitally signed quarterly financial statements, the recipients of the documents can be sure of the identity of the sender and the integrity of the financial information.{br}
You can specify a default certificate that will be used for signing all the PDF documents generated by the system. You use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201060|SM201060]) form to specify a default certificate.{br}
In addition, you (or any other user of your Acumatica ERP instance) can select another certificate to be used as a personal certificate on the [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\SM_20_30_10|User Profile] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203010|SM203010]) form. For a user with a personal certificate, the personal certificate is used instead of the default certificate for signing PDF documents when the user creates PDF documents in the system. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\SM_20_30_10|User Profile] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203010|SM203010]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_60|Security Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201060|SM201060]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_30|Encryption Certificates] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200530|SM200530]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_05_35|Certificate Replacement] ([~/?ScreenId=SM200535|SM200535]) *[HelpRoot_Administration\US__How_to_Import_Digital_Certificate|To Import Certificates] *[HelpRoot_Administration\US__How_to_Encrypt_Database|To Encrypt the Database]

