*[HelpRoot_Administration\EM__HOW_To_Create_a_System_Email_Account|To Create a System Email Account]

In Acumatica ERP, all incoming mail that is received by system email accounts is processed in a series of consecutive steps.{br}
The processing of incoming emails consists of the basic processing, which is enabled out of the box and cannot be additionally configured, and the advanced processing that can be set up individually for each system email account.{br}
This topic describes the rules that the system follows when processing incoming emails and how you can set up this functionality.{br}{TOC} ==Basic Processing== The basic processing consists of the following steps, which are performed by default upon each email received by a system email account:[anchor|#_aea7b8b0-bce4-4a67-9cd3-4521919d405a] #Based on a received email, the system creates an email in Acumatica ERP, with the sender&rsquo;s name, sender&rsquo;s email address, subject, and description specified. The email has the ''Pending Processing'' status and the current date specified as the start date. #If the sender is recognized as an employee, the system assigns that employee as the owner of the email. (The system does not verify whether the employee has the ''Active'' status.) #The system analyzes hidden tags attached to the email and determines if the email has a parent activity in Acumatica ERP. If such an activity is found, the email becomes linked to it and also associated with the related entity, contact, business account, owner, and workgroup (if any) from the parent activity. (When assigning the owner, the system does not verify whether the employee has the ''Active'' status.)
==Advanced Processing== Depending on your business, the mail you receive through Acumatica ERP may consist of requests for information, emails related to customer contracts, or emails received from contacts or leads as replies to emails sent during specific marketing campaigns. You can configure incoming mail processing so that based on an incoming email, the system creates a case or a lead and attaches the email to the created entity as a related activity. Also, an incoming email may be attached to an existing lead, contact, or business account that is related to the email exchange. You can activate and configure the processing of incoming mail individually for each of the system email accounts. You can also specify an email assignment map, which the system will use when it cannot assign incoming emails based on email history. All these options are included in the advanced functionality of incoming mail processing.{br}
You can activate the processing of incoming mail by selecting the required account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_02|System Email Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=SM204002|SM204002]) form, and then selecting the '''Incoming Mail Processing''' check box on the '''Incoming Mail Processing''' tab. ((({S:Warn}Before you activate this processing, make sure that email addresses are specified for all employees involved in customer support and CRM activities on either the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_30_00|Employees] ([~/?ScreenId=EP203000|EP203000]) form or the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form. ))){br}
The advanced processing can be divided into two parts: the mandatory part, which is executed whenever processing is enabled for the system email account, and the optional part, which you can tailor through the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_02|System Email Accounts] form to fit your needs.{br}
The mandatory part includes the following steps, if the related entity that is linked to the email is a case with the ''Open'' or ''Pending Customer'' status and if the email sender is not the owner of the case:[anchor|#_99fa01a8-dfa0-435f-bbbb-98ca6f467610] #The status of the case changes to ''Open'' with the reason set to ''Updated''. #A notification about the updated status is sent to the case owner. #:((({S:Hint}No such notification is sent if the incoming email is a part of internal communication between employees. )))
The optional part includes the following steps, which you can configure by using the '''Incoming Mail Processing''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_02|System Email Accounts] form:[anchor|#ul_nyd_thw_v3] *''Initial processing'': You can configure the system to confirm the receipt of incoming emails by sending replies based on a specific template created through the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_03|Notification Templates] ([~/?ScreenId=SM204003|SM204003]) form. *''Main Processing'': You can select options corresponding to any of the following actions: **Create a new case for each processed email and attach the email to the case as a related activity. **Route the email to the email addresses specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_30_00|Employees] ([~/?ScreenId=EP203000|EP203000]) form for the owners of the parent activity (the owner of the outgoing email to which the sender of the incoming email has replied), related entity (such as the opportunity, contact, or case), and associated business account. **:((({S:Warn}Emails are routed to only those employees that have the '''Route Emails''' check box selected on the '''General Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_30_00|Employees] ([~/?ScreenId=EP203000|EP203000]) form. Emails are not sent to deleted employees or to employees that have the ''Inactive'' status. ))) **Attach each processed email to the business account, contact, or lead related to the email exchange. **Create a new lead for each processed email and attach the email to the lead as a related activity. **Reply to unassigned emails by using a specific template created through the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_03|Notification Templates] form. *''Final processing'': You can decide whether the system should remove processed messages and whether it should add available source information to the bottom of each processed email.
==Processing Steps== Depending on the selected options, the system processes each email as follows (skipping the step if the corresponding option is not selected or if it is not applicable):[anchor|#ul_ggc_nfq_v3] #A receipt confirmation is generated and sent to the email sender. #The email undergoes the basic processing steps. #The system updates the status of the linked case. #The email is routed to the email addresses of the relevant employees. #A new case is created based on the email information. #The email is attached to the business account, contact, or lead related to the email exchange. #A notification is sent to the case owner. #An automatic reply is sent if the system has failed to assign the email. #The email is deleted if the specified conditions are met. #If the email remains unassigned, the system uses the email assignment map specified on the '''Assignment Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_02|System Email Accounts] form to assign the email. #A new lead is created based on the email sender. ((({S:Warn}Generally, the subjects for outgoing mass emails are system-generated and contain values from particular contact records, cases, and activities that will help later with processing replies to the emails if addressees do not change the email subjects. ))) ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Administration\EP__con_Email_Management|Managing Emails]

 Acumatica ERP provides email management functionality to employees involved in customer relationship management (CRM) activities, such as working with leads and contacts, organizing campaigns, and handling cases.{br}

In Acumatica ERP, users can use their favorite email programs for communication with customer contacts and leads, and use their personal email accounts if these email addresses are registered with the system.{br}

For every user involved in CRM or case processing, you should specify the user&rsquo;s personal email account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_30_00|Employees] ([~/?ScreenId=EP203000|EP203000]) form, the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form, or both forms. If incoming mail processing is activated for a system email account, before the system forwards incoming emails to a specific employee, it checks whether the employee has an email address specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_30_00|Employees] form; if there is no such address, the system uses the email address specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] form. {br}

On the [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\SM_20_30_10|User Profile] ([~/?ScreenId=SM203010|SM203010]) form, the user can create a signature, which will be inserted at the end of each email this user sends. The '''Email Settings''' tab provides a text box and a toolbar with tools to format the text of the signature. For more details, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__con_Personal_Document_Processing|Personal Settings for Document Processing]. {br}

On the forms used for creating emails, personal email addresses are available for selection (that is, they appear on the '''From''' list) to only their owners.{br}

 Acumatica ERP tracks the history of email exchanges—that is, the system stores all emails along with references to the related entities (such as contacts or cases). This history is used for automatic processing of incoming emails. For more info, see [HelpRoot_Administration\EM__con_Email_Exchange_History|Email Exchange History].{br}

Users can use templates for their emails or set up automatic notifications based on specific templates. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\EM__con_Notification_Templates|Notification Templates].{br}

For each system email account, you can manually initiate the processes of sending and receiving mail, or you can set up an automatic schedule for these processes. Also, you can suspend sending and receiving emails for all system email accounts at once. For more info, see [HelpRoot_Administration\EM__con_Sending_and_Receiving_Emails|Mail Sending and Receipt].{br}

To prevent the system from slowing down due to a large number of emails, both incoming and outgoing, accumulated over a long time, you can archive processed emails. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\EM__con_Email_Archiving|Email Archiving].
