==To Create the Custom Theme for Acumatica ERP==[anchor|#_5d87b959-cdde-4aca-9939-0b17da89d6cf]
#Navigate to the <tt>App&#95;Themes</tt> folder of the site you want to change the theme of and open it.
#Copy the <tt>Default</tt> folder and paste it into the <tt>App&#95;Themes</tt> folder to make the custom theme be visible for the system.
#Type a custom name for the copied folder, such as <tt>Chicago</tt>, and then open it.
#Navigate to the <tt>Content</tt> folder of the site you want to change the theme of and open it.
#Copy the <tt>Site.css</tt> file, and paste it into the same folder.
#Specify the name for the copied file as follows: Type <tt>Site</tt> immediately followed by a text string with the name of the theme that you created in Steps 1–3 of the current procedure; do not use any spaces in the line. For instance, if you had specified the {{Chicago}} title for the new theme folder, here you would type <tt>SiteChicago</tt>.
#Open the copied file, and make the needed changes in the code to affect the look of the UI elements. You can perform any of the following actions:
#*If you want to change the background color of the header, find the {{.navbar.master}} selector, and specify the required value for the {{background-color:}} property, as shown in the following sample code.{{{{.navbar.master
{
  min-height: 50px;
  font-size: 11pt;
  background-color: #007acc;
}
}}}}
#*If you want to change the color of the main menu icons, find the {{.list-group.modules .ac, .list-group.modules .svg-icon}} selector, and specify the required value for the {{color:}} property, as shown in the following sample code.{{{{.list-group.modules .ac, .list-group.modules .svg-icon 
{
  font-size: 20pt;
  color: #0078D7;
}
}}}}
#*If you want to change the background color of the tiles on the working area, find the {{.top-links > a}} selector, and specify the required value for the <tt>background-color:</tt> property, as shown in the following sample code. {{{{.top-links &gt; a 
{
      position: relative;
      float: left;
      font-size: 11pt;
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 10px;
      margin-right: 15px;
      margin-top: 10px;
      width: 135px;
      height: 80px;
      background-color: #007acc;
      color: white;
      border-radius: 2px;
}
}}}}
#*If you want to change the color of the tile font, specify the required value for the <tt>color:</tt> property of the {{.top-links > a}} selector.
#*If you want to change the background color of the footer, find the {{.lic-banner}} selector and specify the required value for the <tt>background-color:</tt> property: {{{{.lic-banner 
{
      position: relative;
      padding: 5px 15px;
      height: 30px;
      background-color: #007acc;
      color: white;
}
}}}}
#*If you want to change the color of the footer font, specify the required value for the {{color:}} property of the {{.lic-banner}} selector.
#Save your changes to the file.
#Navigate to Site Preferences (SM200505) form of the Acumatica ERP.
#In the '''Interface Theme''' box of the '''General Defaults''' section, select the name of the theme you have created (such as ''Chicago'' in the example in this topic).
#Click '''Save''' on the form toolbar.

To Change the Default Theme of  Acumatica ERPIn  Acumatica ERP, you can change the color theme by selecting the appropriate one on the   ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) Site Preferences (SM200505) form. The system provides two predefined                 themes:  Default  (which is initially applied) and  Indigo .  If the company wants to apply a custom theme, the administrator can create and then                 apply it on the   ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) Site Preferences form. Before You Proceed Make sure that you have administrative access to the   ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) Site Preferences                 (SM200505) form so that you can change the interface theme. To Change the Theme in  Acumatica ERPOpen the   ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) Site Preferences (SM200505) form. In the  Interface Theme  box of the  General                         Defaults  section, select the theme you want to apply to the                     system. Click  Save  on the form toolbar. To Specify a Custom Color for the Site User Interface Open the   ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) Site Preferences (SM200505) form. In the  Interface Theme  box of the  General                         Defaults  section, select the  Default  theme. In the  Primary Color  box, do any of the following:  Click the color box to open the  Colors  dialog box                             and select the color to be used for the user interface. Close the dialog                             box to confirm the color selection. In the box next to the color selection box, enter the hexadecimal number                             of the color you want to apply to the user interface. On the   ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) Site Preferences form toolbar, click                          Save  to apply the changes. To Reset a Custom Primary Color for the Default Theme  Open the   ([~/?ScreenId=SM200505|SM200505]) Site Preferences (SM200505) form. In the  Interface Theme  box of the  General                         Defaults  section, make sure the  Default  theme is                     selected. Next to the  Interface Theme  box, click the                          Reset to Default Colors  button In the  Confirm Color Reset  dialog box click OK to confirm                     the action. To Specify a Custom Color for a Specific Company Open the   ([~/?ScreenId=CS101500|CS101500]) Companies (CS101500) form. Click the company ID of the company for which you want to override colors to                     open its settings. In the  Theme  section of the  Visual                         Appearance  tab, select the  Override Colors for the                         Selected Company  check box. In the  Primary Color  box, do any of the following:  Click the color box to open the  Colors  dialog box                             and select the color to be used for the user interface. Close the dialog                             box to confirm the color selection. In the box next to the color selection box, enter the hexadecimal number                             of the color you want to apply to the user interface. On the form toolbar, click  Save . To Specify a Custom Color for a Specific Branch Open the   ([~/?ScreenId=CS102000|CS102000]) Branches (CS102000) form. Click the branch ID of the branch for which you want to override colors to open                     its settings. In the  Theme  section of the  Visual                         Appearance  tab, select the  Override Colors for the                         Selected Branch  check box. In the  Primary Color  box, do any of the following:  Click the color box to open the  Colors  dialog box                             and select the color to be used for the user interface. Close the dialog                             box to confirm the color selection. In the box next to the color selection box, enter the hexadecimal number                             of the color you want to apply to the user interface. On the form toolbar, click  Save . Before You Proceed To create a custom theme, make sure that you have the access rights to add, delete,                 or modify the files of the  Acumatica ERP database that is located on the server.  To Create the Custom Theme for  Acumatica ERPNavigate to the  App_Themes  folder of the site you want to                     change the theme of and open it. Copy the  Default  folder and paste it into the                          App_Themes  folder to make the custom theme be visible                     for the system. Type a custom name for the copied folder, such as                      Chicago , and then open it. Navigate to the  Content  folder of the site you want to                     change the theme of and open it. Copy the  Site.css  file, and paste it into the same                     folder. Specify the name for the copied file as follows: Type                          Site  immediately followed by a text string with the                     name of the theme that you created in Steps 1–3 of the current procedure;                     do not use any spaces in the line. For instance, if you had specified the                          Chicago  title for the new theme folder, here you would type                          SiteChicago . Open the copied file, and make the needed changes in the code to affect the look                     of the UI elements. You can perform any of the following actions: If you want to change the background color of the header, find the                                  .navbar.master  selector, and specify the required                             value for the  background-color:  property, as shown in                             the following sample                             code. .navbar.master
{
  min-height: 50px;
  font-size: 11pt;
  background-color: #007acc;
} If you want to change the color of the main menu icons, find the                                  .list-group.modules .ac, .list-group.modules                                 .svg-icon  selector, and specify the required value for the                                  color:  property, as shown in the following sample                             code. .list-group.modules .ac, .list-group.modules .svg-icon 
{
  font-size: 20pt;
  color: #0078D7;
} If you want to change the background color of the tiles on the working                             area, find the  .top-links > a  selector, and specify the                             required value for the  background-color:  property, as                             shown in the following sample code.                              .top-links > a 
{
      position: relative;
      float: left;
      font-size: 11pt;
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 10px;
      margin-right: 15px;
      margin-top: 10px;
      width: 135px;
      height: 80px;
      background-color: #007acc;
      color: white;
      border-radius: 2px;
} If you want to change the color of the tile font, specify the required                             value for the  color:  property of the                                  .top-links > a  selector. If you want to change the background color of the footer, find the                                  .lic-banner  selector and specify the required value                             for the  background-color:  property:                              .lic-banner 
{
      position: relative;
      padding: 5px 15px;
      height: 30px;
      background-color: #007acc;
      color: white;
