When an article is also a folder, the article appears as a node in the wiki tree and may contain articles. ==To Define an Article as a Folder== You can define a new or existing article as a folder. For more information about creating a new folder—that is, creating an article and defining it as a folder—see [HelpRoot_Administration\DM__how_Wiki_Creating_a_New_Article|To Add an Article]. To define an existing article as a folder, do the following: [anchor|#ol_s51_f2z_mj] #Open the article. #On the wiki toolbar, click '''Edit''' to open the Wiki Editor form. #On the '''Content''' tab, select the '''Folder''' check box. #On the Wiki Editor form toolbar, click '''Save'''.
After you have defined an article as a folder, if you open the article in the Wiki Editor form, you can see the '''Subarticles''' tab. ==To Add Articles to a Folder== You can populate a folder with articles by moving existing articles into the folder or by creating new articles in the folder. To move existing articles to the folder, use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_20_10|Wiki Site Map] ([~/?ScreenId=SM202010|SM202010]) form. If you're creating a new article, open the article in the Wiki Editor form, and on the '''Contents''' tab, specify the folder in the '''Parent Folder''' box. ==To Convert a Folder into an Article== A folder can be converted to an article only if the folder doesn&rsquo;t contain any articles. For more information about moving the articles to another folder, see [HelpRoot_Administration\DM__how_Wiki_Moving_an_Article_to_Another_Folder|To Move an Article].{br}
