Some processes in Acumatica ERP require multiple tasks to be executed to complete the whole process. These include the processes of implementing the Acumatica ERP modules (one-time processes), or business processes performed in different modules, such as closing the financial periods in the modules of the Finance suite (recurrent processes).{br}

The business process scenarios tool gives you the ability to simplify the execution of such complex processes. By using this tool, you can create a scenario that contains the list of tasks required for completing some process. Executing the scenario according to these tasks allows you to control the execution of the whole process.{br}

Each scenario has a hierarchical structure. You can create the tasks and subtasks, and set the order of their execution (if needed), which depends on the system configuration, your enabled features, or your business needs.{br}

While configuring a scenario, you can apply the role-based approach by specifying an access role for each scenario. By using this approach, you can manage an access to every scenario, so that only the users that are granted by this role can access it.{br}

This chapter describes the functionality of the business process scenarios tool and provides details about using this tool by considering the example of the recurrent process that is performed in Acumatica ERP. 
