As you use Acumatica ERP, you may need to perform various complex procedures on a regular basis. These procedures can include multiple tasks that need to be executed. This chapter describes an example of a business process that is performed in the Accounts Receivable module regularly: closing the financial period.{br}
Before closing a financial period, the user has to check that all required tasks are executed, required documents are released, all open payments are applied, and necessary reports and statements are prepared. Thus, to account for all possibilities, you need to do the following:[anchor|#ul_qly_mmk_cp] *Compose the list of tasks. *Create a scenario in the system and add these tasks to it.
This chapter describes the prepared list of tasks that have to be executed before closing of the financial period in the Accounts Receivable module, and use of the business process wizard tool to complete the process.

row.column:
In this topic and the steps within it, you can find a detailed description of the steps you need to perform to resolve performance issues on the client side and, if necessary, to gather information to provide it to the Acumatica support team. {br}
Performance issues fall into two broad categories:[anchor|#_8ed1d57a-489d-4768-a749-1630d005340f] *'''Overall performance is slow''' *:The whole site is slow, and you cannot identify a particular process for which the slowdown occurs. *'''Some process works slowly''' *:The site works slowly when a user is working with particular forms or executing specific actions. {br}
The category your client’s performance issues fall into dictates the steps and substeps you should perform to find the reasons for the performance slowdown and resolve the issue. For each category, the following table shows these steps and substeps; the + symbol indicates that you should perform the step or substep. You can find detailed descriptions of the steps and substeps in the applicable topics.[anchor|#_f928024f-0488-4c44-912e-c221d66be52a] ===Performance Troubleshooting=== {| class="checklist" | width="100%" |- !width="33%" ! !width="33%" ! Overall performance is slow !width="33%" ! Some process works slowly |- | colspan="3" | [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step1|Step 1: Check the most basic causes] |- | 1. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step1#_36238980-f793-4d0d-8b88-4cbcb9b6077b|Check whether the site is licensed] | + | Skip this substep |- | 2. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step1#_cacf2a39-2ffa-4729-af83-da68d6845964|Check the speed from other browsers] | + | + |- | 3. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step1#_e8fa44f8-311c-4d2a-a2e2-aabed4a155d5|Check the speed from other locations] | + | + |- | 4. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step1#_3f2ef842-3b6a-4c79-9be7-99cbb953f227|Check automation schedules] | + | + |- | 5. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step1#_ba43ed97-9782-4aea-9b48-820b14cfb5fe|Explore the running processes] | + | + |- | 6. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step1#_8d5338a1-c780-4797-8728-a786fbf92abb|Check whether antivirus software is blocking some functionality of the site] | + | Skip this substep |- | [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step2|Step 2: Investigate application server time and database server time in the Request Profiler] | + | Skip this step |- | [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step3|Step 3: Check the configuration of the application server] | + | Skip this step |- | colspan="3" | [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step4|Step 4.1: Check the Configuration of Microsoft SQL Server and Run Reports] |- | 1. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step4#_0a4969cd-273f-48b6-8db0-a806663603b3|Check the configuration of the database server] | + | + |- | 2. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step4#_370d83b1-6a5c-415a-b461-20adae300041|Run performance reports] | + | + |- | 3. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step4#_f0ec98d2-edc3-4c3e-928f-234b3860aae5|Check the SQL Activity Monitor for locks] | + | + |- | [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step42|Step 4.2: Check the Configuration of MySQL Database Server] | + | + |- | colspan="3" | [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step5|Step 5: Collect more information] |- | 1. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step5#_2eccbfeb-aafd-4ac5-a947-f551b22077e4|Investigate requests in the Request Profiler] | + | + |- | 2. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step5#_fef30de7-dc42-43f4-aca5-14f7f616d1ad|Collect additional information from the logs] | + | + |- | 3. [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step5#_991d93b5-7072-411d-afec-6d666b7ef042|Use external tools] | + | + |- | [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step6|Step 6: Submit a case to Acumatica support] | + | + |}

To exclude the reasons that lead to performance slowdown most frequently, you should perform the substeps described in the sections that follow.[anchor|#_36238980-f793-4d0d-8b88-4cbcb9b6077b] ==1. Check Whether the Site Is Licensed== The slowdown may be caused by the site not being licensed. Sites in trial mode allow only two concurrent users and limit the usage of hardware resources. {br}
If you have already registered the site, it could become unlicensed for the following reasons:[anchor|#_30b48afd-9009-4880-a0ed-9970400458eb] *A user may be using a URL of an unregistered site—for example, if the user is accessing the site through a bookmark with that URL. *Some hardware changes have been made to the application server—for example, more CPUs have been added, or the application pools have been changed. {br}
Perform the following task to check whether the site is licensed.'''To check whether the site is licensed:'''[anchor|#_f9e44184-76ae-47a3-9a7b-6c58183c3edc] #Check if the site is licensed in one of the following ways: #*Make sure there is no message in the bottom of the browser window that says ''Your product is in the trial mode. Only two concurrent users are allowed. Activate''. See the message in the following screenshot. #*On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_15_10|Activate License] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201510|SM201510]) form, check the value of the '''Status''' element. An unregistered site has the ''Invalid'' status, as shown in the following screenshot.[anchor|#_47b6c4ba-82d7-4d0c-9e9f-aabcab40ac9e][image:UserGuide/Images/ActivateLicenseInvalid.png|popup|Invalid license|450px] #Depending on the results of the previous instruction, do one of the following: #*If the site is not licensed, activate the license by following the instructions in [HelpRoot_Install\Licensing_Acumatica|Licensing and Activating Acumatica ERP]. #*If the site is licensed, continue with the next substep. [anchor|#_cacf2a39-2ffa-4729-af83-da68d6845964] ==2. Check the Speed from Other Browsers== Another possible reason for the slowdown is that some properties of the browser may be preventing the site from running faster.{br}
Perform the following task to see whether this is the reason for the slowdown.{br}
'''To check the speed from other browsers:'''[anchor|#_32bf72be-e3af-4daf-879f-994f4c70655d] #Try to access the site from another browser. #Depending on the results of the previous instruction, do one of the following: #*If the issue is reproduced in only one browser, check the version of the browser, and try to reproduce the issue in the latest version of the browser. You can also try to turn off plug-ins in the browser. Collect more information on the slowdown, and send it to the Acumatica support team, as described in [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step5|Step 5: Collect More Information] and [HelpRoot_Administration\how_Troubleshoot_Performance_Step6|Step 6: Submit a Case to Acumatica Support]. #*If the issue is reproduced in all browsers, continue with the next substep. [anchor|#_e8fa44f8-311c-4d2a-a2e2-aabed4a155d5] ==3. Check the Speed from Other Locations== Some network or internet service provider issues at the user’s end may be causing a performance slowdown.{br}
